{
  "text": "As a starting point, here, we will use the SDBI+FI action expressed in the non-linear formalism, where the complete action can be written explicitly in terms of variables appropriate for the nonlinear supersymmetry but at the cost of losing manifest invariance under linear supersymmetry [CITATION_1] . We will first expand it in components in section 2.1 and then use field redefinitions to spell out the on-shell physical interactions with dimension less than 12, as well as all dimension-12 operators of the form (\u03bb\u2202\u03bb)F 4 in section 2.2. The result suggests that on-shell the FI term plays a trivial role and can be absorbed by redefining the brane tension.",
  "citation_candidates": [
